Talk louder.

411
00:17:20.331 --> 00:17:24.042  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I’m just saying if we give in
to every impulse, we’re
no better than wild animals.

412
00:17:24.126 --> 00:17:26.587  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
But if we push it down,
it eats you alive.

413
00:17:26.671 --> 00:17:28.046  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
Not if you just let it go.

414
00:17:28.130 --> 00:17:29.840  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
The chick from that crapfest
<i>Mary Poppins.</i>

415
00:17:29.924 --> 00:17:31.634  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
That’s it.

416
00:17:33.552 --> 00:17:35.387  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:75.93% 
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

417
00:17:33.552 --> 00:17:35.387  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
[ Grunting ]

418
00:17:35.471 --> 00:17:39.474  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
A lot of cold, lonely nights
in that apartment by myself
while my mom was driving a taxi,

419
00:17:39.558 --> 00:17:41.393  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
and only one thing
kept me company.

420
00:17:41.477 --> 00:17:45.064  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
So you got a problem
with Poppins,
you got a problem with me.

421
00:17:46.565 --> 00:17:48.775  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>Ay,</i> Father,
I am so sorry.

422
00:17:48.859 --> 00:17:50.903  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
I didn’t even know
that he could hold a fork.

423
00:17:50.987 --> 00:17:52.696  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
No, no, no.
I blame myself.

424
00:17:52.780 --> 00:17:54.573  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I probably shouldn’t
have taken his nose.

425
00:17:54.657 --> 00:17:56.575  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
No, it’s my family.

426
00:17:56.659 --> 00:18:00.579  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
The girls are very chesty,
but the men–
they’re kissed by the devil.

427
00:18:00.663 --> 00:18:03.040  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Gloria, the fact
that you are so concerned...

428
00:18:03.124 --> 00:18:06.084  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
is only proof that you are
a loving and caring mother.

429
00:18:06.168 --> 00:18:09.046  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
It’s the parents
who shape the child.

430
00:18:09.130 --> 00:18:11.632  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:69.06% 
[ Joe Giggling ]

431
00:18:09.130 --> 00:18:11.632  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:84.23% 
And your son is growing up
in a wonderful home.

432
00:18:11.716 --> 00:18:13.926  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:75.93% 
Die, scum!

433
00:18:11.716 --> 00:18:13.926  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
No, no, no!

434
00:18:14.010 --> 00:18:15.636  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Louder, like you did
at the drive-through.

435
00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:18.263  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:84.33% 
Mom, Jay and I
saw <i>Death Wish.</i> Amazing.

436
00:18:18.347 --> 00:18:21.266  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Manny got in a fight
at <i>The Sound of Music,</i>
got kicked out.

437
00:18:21.350 --> 00:18:23.644  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
I’ve never been so proud.

438
00:18:23.728 --> 00:18:27.147  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, I guess every household
could use a little fine-tuning,
huh?

439
00:18:27.231 --> 00:18:29.775  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:70.50% 
Let me give you my card
with my cell number on it.

440
00:18:27.231 --> 00:18:29.775  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
Please.

441
00:18:29.859 --> 00:18:31.610  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
And what did I do
with my wallet?

442
00:18:31.694 --> 00:18:33.988  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:5.00%  line:75.93% 
I–

443
00:18:31.694 --> 00:18:33.988  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
[ Joe Coos ]

444
00:18:41.871 --> 00:18:44.706  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
I had yelled at Phil
for not helping out,
and there he was,

445
00:18:44.790 --> 00:18:47.167  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
doing exactly
what I had asked him to do.

446
00:18:47.251 --> 00:18:50.963  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
There’s our zucchini.
Up top, buddy.

447
00:18:51.047 --> 00:18:52.881  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
For some other family.

448
00:18:52.965 --> 00:18:55.133  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
You are so sweet
for helping me with this.

449
00:18:55.217 --> 00:18:56.969  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
How hurt you’ve been,
Lorraine.

450
00:18:57.053 --> 00:18:59.889  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
This is sweet.
This is... normal.

451
00:19:00.681 --> 00:19:03.392  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:84.33% 
- Phil?
- Diane?

452
00:19:03.476 --> 00:19:05.978  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
Hey, superstar.

453
00:19:03.476 --> 00:19:05.978  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:89.66% 
I thought I was superstar.

454
00:19:06.062 --> 00:19:08.105  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, your husband
has been so wonderful to me.

455
00:19:08.189 --> 00:19:09.648  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
He’s not my husband.
He’s my Realtor.

456
00:19:09.732 --> 00:19:11.942  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:75.93% 
Oh, he’s my Realtor.

457
00:19:09.732 --> 00:19:11.942  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.66% 
I’m both your Realtors.

458
00:19:12.026 --> 00:19:15.028  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:73.67% 
I’m just lucky to have such a–
 
We’re on our way
to an open house.

459
00:19:15.112 --> 00:19:17.489  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
Oh, is that why
you couldn’t show me
the colonial later?

460
00:19:17.573 --> 00:19:19.074  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
I made that corn bread
that you like.

461
00:19:19.158 --> 00:19:21.660  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
We’re gonna make it to that.
I just have to finish up
with Lorraine.

462
00:19:21.744 --> 00:19:24.121  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
- Oh, you mean, like,
"get it over with"?
- No, I don’t mean that.

463
00:19:24.205 --> 00:19:27.332  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
And I thought zucchini bread
was your favorite, or why–
why am I buying zucchini?

464
00:19:27.416 --> 00:19:30.168  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Hey, can’t a guy like
zucchini bread and corn bread?

465
00:19:30.252 --> 00:19:32.087  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:70.50% 
[ Woman ]
Phil?

466
00:19:30.252 --> 00:19:32.087  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
Damn it.

467
00:19:32.171 --> 00:19:34.715  position:80.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:69.06% 
Ronnie!

468
00:19:32.171 --> 00:19:34.715  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.23% 
I thought you had
a doctor’s appointment.

469
00:19:34.799 --> 00:19:36.967  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
That’s why you had to miss
Darrell’s swim meet.

470
00:19:37.051 --> 00:19:38.927  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:75.93% 
Who’s she?

471
00:19:37.051 --> 00:19:38.927  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.66% 
Just another client.

472
00:19:39.011 --> 00:19:41.805  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
- "Just another client"?
- No, that’s–
What is this?

473
00:19:41.889 --> 00:19:44.016  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
Uh-oh. It is.
It’s my office.

474
00:19:44.100 --> 00:19:45.809  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:84.33% 
Got to take it.
Hello?

475
00:19:45.893 --> 00:19:48.186  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:84.33% 
- Phil?
- Claire?

476
00:19:48.270 --> 00:19:50.439  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
World’s greatest Realtor!

477
00:19:50.523 --> 00:19:51.940  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
What are you doing here?

478
00:19:52.024 --> 00:19:53.608  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Your hair is sweating.

479
00:19:53.692 --> 00:19:55.694  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
That’s ’cause I’m excited
to see my friends.

480
00:19:55.778 --> 00:19:57.529  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Let’s go, buddy.

481
00:19:57.613 --> 00:19:59.865  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Claire ]
Are you all
clients of Phil’s?

482
00:19:59.949 --> 00:20:01.408  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:75.93% 
Apparently.

483
00:19:59.949 --> 00:20:01.408  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
Uh-oh.

484
00:20:01.492 --> 00:20:03.618  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
You could not be
in better hands.

485
00:20:03.702 --> 00:20:07.039  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
I met Phil when I was
at such a rocky place
in my life.

486
00:20:07.123 --> 00:20:09.916  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:84.33% 
He was available to me
morning, noon and night.

487
00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:13.253  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Of course he found me
my dream house,
but that wasn’t the best part.

488
00:20:13.337 --> 00:20:17.049  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Phil taught me
how to trust a man again,

489
00:20:17.133 --> 00:20:19.051  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
and I think that was
always his plan.

490
00:20:19.135 --> 00:20:21.345  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:75.93% 
That was always my plan.

491
00:20:19.135 --> 00:20:21.345  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
Mmm.

492
00:20:21.429 --> 00:20:25.098  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
And it was not easy for me
to trust a man
after the husband that I’d had.

493
00:20:25.182 --> 00:20:29.019  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
This guys left tools
in the yard,
let the kids run wild.

494
00:20:29.103 --> 00:20:31.480  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:50.00%  line:69.06% 
Well, great to see you, Claire.

495
00:20:29.103 --> 00:20:31.480  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.23% 
He was always
interrupting me.

496
00:20:31.564 --> 00:20:34.775  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
And he wore the most ridiculous
sleep mask thing.

497
00:20:34.859 --> 00:20:37.069  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, God!
Sounds like such a diva.

498
00:20:37.153 --> 00:20:40.238  position:45.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:69.06% 
Yeah.

499
00:20:37.153 --> 00:20:40.238  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.23% 
Or he’s photosensitive,
which is a real condition.

500
00:20:40.322 --> 00:20:42.824  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
He never took my advice.
You know, that’s the worst part.

501
00:20:42.908 --> 00:20:45.702  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
He never– He never said he was
sorry just one time.

502
00:20:45.786 --> 00:20:50.415  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
I would kill to have heard,
"Claire, you were right."

503
00:20:50.499 --> 00:20:51.833  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:75.93% 
[ Groans ]

504
00:20:50.499 --> 00:20:51.833  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.66% 
[ Diane Chuckles ]

505
00:20:51.917 --> 00:20:53.919  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:89.67% 
She was right.

506
00:20:54.003 --> 00:20:55.670  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Louder!

507
00:20:55.754 --> 00:20:58.048  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
I do not love this side of you.

508
00:21:02.386 --> 00:21:04.054  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
Thanks for winning
my computer back.

509
00:21:04.138 --> 00:21:06.390  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:5.00% 
And getting me all my money.
That was awesome.

510
00:21:06.474 --> 00:21:09.726  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:5.00% 
Yeah, if only
I had stopped there,
but I had to go back down.

511
00:21:09.810 --> 00:21:11.686  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:5.00% 
I got greedy,
and I was careless.

512
00:21:11.770 --> 00:21:14.356  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
There’s a story about that
I remember from school.

513
00:21:14.440 --> 00:21:17.859  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:5.00% 
Icarus flew too close
to his son.

514
00:21:17.943 --> 00:21:20.112  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:5.00% 
I think their wings bumped.
One of them fell.

515
00:21:20.196 --> 00:21:22.280  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:5.00% 
They might have been ducks.
Anyway, the lesson is...

516
00:21:22.364 --> 00:21:23.990  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:5.00% 
is that you have
to pay attention.
 
[ Doorbell Rings ]

517
00:21:24.074 --> 00:21:25.868  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:5.00% 
Or pay the ultimate price.

518
00:21:27.286 --> 00:21:28.662  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:5.00% 
Shall we, my dear?

519
00:21:28.746 --> 00:21:30.998  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:5.00% 
Don’t wait up.

520
00:21:28.746 --> 00:21:30.998  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:18.74% 
